FBIS4-51871 "dreas086_c_94025" FBIS-EAS-94-086 Daily Report 1 May 1994 North Korea More Reports on Kim Il-song Birthday Activities More Reports on Kim Il-song Birthday Activities More Foreign Party Leaders Greetings SK0105082494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0806 GMT 1 May 94 SK0105082494 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, May 1 (KCNA) -- The great leader President Kim Il-song received messages of greetings from foreign party leaders on the occasion of his birthday. The messages came from James Stewart, general secretary, and Eoin O'Murku, international secretary, of the National Executive Committee of the Communist Party of Ireland, Roberto Gabriele, general secretary of the Italian Movement for Peace and Socialism, Juan Ramos, general secretary of the Communist Party of the Peoples of Spain, Michael Hicks, general secretary of the Britannic Communist Party, Rolf Hagel, chairman of the Workers' Party- Communists of Sweden, Ludo Martens, chairman of the Central Committee of the Belgian Labour Party, and Dilip Barua, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Bangladesh (Marxist-Leninist). President Kim Il-song also received a message of greetings from the Central Committee of the Norwegian Communist Party on the same occasion. The messages extended warmest congratulations to President Kim Il-song and wished him good health and a long life. They expressed firm solidarity for the Korean people's struggle to defend the sovereignty and peace of their country and achieve national reunification in a peaceful way.
